            <content:encoded><![CDATA[https://kotaku.com/marvel-rivals-best-vanguards-ps-vr2-best-games-1851737103<br/><br/><div id="readability-page-1" class="page"><div><div><figure id="" data-id="e4afc108faa66841237832b4d53dd4b5" data-recommend-id="image://e4afc108faa66841237832b4d53dd4b5" data-format="jpg" data-width="1280" data-height="720" data-lightbox="false" data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="false" data-imagerights="in-house-art" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->WB / DC / Universal / Kotaku<!-- -->, <!-- -->The Pokémon Company / Kotaku<!-- -->, <!-- -->2K / Rebellion / Kotaku<!-- -->, <!-- -->Hyperkin / IGN<!-- -->, <!-- -->Paramount<!-- -->, <!-- -->Marvel Games<!-- -->, <!-- -->Screenshot<!-- -->: <!-- -->Capcom / Kotaku<!-- -->, <!-- -->Sony / Kotaku<!-- -->, <!-- -->Marvel<!-- -->, <!-- -->Sony / Kotaku</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="e4afc108faa66841237832b4d53dd4b5" data-recommend-id="image://e4afc108faa66841237832b4d53dd4b5" data-format="jpg" data-width="1280" data-height="720" data-lightbox="false" data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>This week, our tips and recommendations hodgepodge will point you toward a 4K Blu-ray sale at Amazon that you don’t want to miss, help you get the most out of your PlayStation Portal, and suggest which of <em>Marvel Rivals</em>’ Vanguards will most effectively give you the edge over the competition. Click on for all this and more.</p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="66f0e45d7b11312a925e3aa9d83da9f2" data-recommend-id="image://66f0e45d7b11312a925e3aa9d83da9f2" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="A collage of discounted movies. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="A collage of discounted movies. " data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="fair-use" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->WB / DC / Universal / Kotaku</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="66f0e45d7b11312a925e3aa9d83da9f2" data-recommend-id="image://66f0e45d7b11312a925e3aa9d83da9f2" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="A collage of discounted movies. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>If you have been wanting to build your <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/best-buy-dvd-blu-ray-games-sales-stop-2024-1851136668&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/best-buy-dvd-blu-ray-games-sales-stop-2024-1851136668">physical movie collection</a></span> or just want to watch some new movies for cheap, you should stop what you’re doing and check out Amazon’s fantastic 4K UHD Blu-ray sale featuring old and new movies.  - Zack Zwiezen <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/amazon-4k-uhd-bluray-batman-dune-barbie-joker-godzilla-1851734723?_gl=1*18eci4l*_ga*MzQzNjkwNDM2LjE2NDY2NjQ1NzQ.*_ga_V4QNJTT5L0*MTczNjUzMjA1MC4yNjMuMS4xNzM2NTMzNDY1LjU0LjAuMA..&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/amazon-4k-uhd-bluray-batman-dune-barbie-joker-godzilla-1851734723?_gl=1*18eci4l*_ga*MzQzNjkwNDM2LjE2NDY2NjQ1NzQ.*_ga_V4QNJTT5L0*MTczNjUzMjA1MC4yNjMuMS4xNzM2NTMzNDY1LjU0LjAuMA..">Read More</a></span></p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="41723d8fa30ed0c63b227d19c98784dc" data-recommend-id="image://41723d8fa30ed0c63b227d19c98784dc" data-format="jpg" data-width="1177" data-height="662" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="The Pokemon Center's Year of Eevee banner, featuring drawings of all nine types." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="The Pokemon Center's Year of Eevee banner, featuring drawings of all nine types." data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="other-license" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->The Pokémon Company / Kotaku</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="41723d8fa30ed0c63b227d19c98784dc" data-recommend-id="image://41723d8fa30ed0c63b227d19c98784dc" data-format="jpg" data-width="1177" data-height="662" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="The Pokemon Center's Year of Eevee banner, featuring drawings of all nine types." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>Step aside Luigi, 2025 is now officially the Year of Eevee. That’s the rather bold claim made today on the official <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;External link&quot;,&quot;https://www.pokemoncenter.com/year-of-eevee&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://www.pokemoncenter.com/year-of-eevee" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Pokémon Center  website</a></span>. What does it mean? Well, the TCG is about to launch a new special set of cards called Prismatic Evolutions, all themed around the lil’ brown pup and its octet of evolved forms, with new products released throughout the whole year, and there’s a bunch of new Eevee merch on the store, but could it also be...? - John Walker <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/pokemon-year-of-eevee-prismatic-evolutions-plush-1851732914&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/pokemon-year-of-eevee-prismatic-evolutions-plush-1851732914">Read More</a></span></p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="dcb4ca987de02d377179f6a138c9ec9b" data-recommend-id="image://dcb4ca987de02d377179f6a138c9ec9b" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="fair-use" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->2K / Rebellion / Kotaku</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="dcb4ca987de02d377179f6a138c9ec9b" data-recommend-id="image://dcb4ca987de02d377179f6a138c9ec9b" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>Happy New Year! Did you walk away from Christmas with more games to play and a backlog that seems impossible to chop through? Well, get ready to possibly add even more games to it, as Amazon has announced 16 free games are coming to Prime members in January.  - Zack Zwiezen <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/amazon-prime-gaming-free-pc-steam-games-january-2025-1851736481&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/amazon-prime-gaming-free-pc-steam-games-january-2025-1851736481">Read More</a></span></p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="8174cf05bdffe8b65f930e4fac5ffcda" data-recommend-id="image://8174cf05bdffe8b65f930e4fac5ffcda" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Leon fires at hostile villagers with a gun in first-person." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="Leon fires at hostile villagers with a gun in first-person." data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="fair-use" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Screenshot<!-- -->: <!-- -->Capcom / Kotaku</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="8174cf05bdffe8b65f930e4fac5ffcda" data-recommend-id="image://8174cf05bdffe8b65f930e4fac5ffcda" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Leon fires at hostile villagers with a gun in first-person." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure></div><div><figure id="" data-id="5a096cb6e5699be41df6d9948b496de5" data-recommend-id="image://5a096cb6e5699be41df6d9948b496de5" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="A PlayStation icon shines in the darkness on a PS Portal." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="A PlayStation icon shines in the darkness on a PS Portal." data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="fair-use" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Screenshot<!-- -->: <!-- -->Sony / Kotaku</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="5a096cb6e5699be41df6d9948b496de5" data-recommend-id="image://5a096cb6e5699be41df6d9948b496de5" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="A PlayStation icon shines in the darkness on a PS Portal." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>The <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;External link&quot;,&quot;https://g-o-media.digidip.net/visit?url=https%3A%2F%2Fdirect.playstation.com%2Fen-us%2Fbuy-accessories%2Fplaystation-portal-remote-player&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://g-o-media.digidip.net/visit?url=https%3A%2F%2Fdirect.playstation.com%2Fen-us%2Fbuy-accessories%2Fplaystation-portal-remote-player" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">PlayStation Portal</a></span> is one hell of a handheld device, capable of streaming games from your PlayStation 5 and directly from Sony’s servers if you’re a PlayStation Plus member). But you probably already know that if you’ve grabbed one for yourself. Instead, you’re probably here to learn the step-by-step process of setting it all up, eh? Or to troubleshoot any strange issues you might encounter when first powering up the device? Fair enough. Lets’ dive into it. - Billy Givens <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/ps-portal-ps5-setup-remote-play-internet-connection-1851735733&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/ps-portal-ps5-setup-remote-play-internet-connection-1851735733">Read More</a></span></p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="968e2130bb63815804619ee4fbfb7185" data-recommend-id="image://968e2130bb63815804619ee4fbfb7185" data-format="jpg" data-width="2289" data-height="1282" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="The Fantastic Four look up at something off-screen." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="The Fantastic Four look up at something off-screen." data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="fair-use" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Screenshot<!-- -->: <!-- -->Marvel</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="968e2130bb63815804619ee4fbfb7185" data-recommend-id="image://968e2130bb63815804619ee4fbfb7185" data-format="jpg" data-width="2289" data-height="1282" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="The Fantastic Four look up at something off-screen." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p><span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/marvel-rivals-review-hero-shooter-overwatch-netease-1851717975&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/marvel-rivals-review-hero-shooter-overwatch-netease-1851717975"><em>Marvel Rivals</em></a></span><em> </em>is entering its second season, confusingly named Season 1 because the first one was Season 0, and it’s bringing four new heroes to the game all at once. The <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/the-fantastic-four-cast-pedro-pascal-vanessa-kirby-mcu-1851256106&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/the-fantastic-four-cast-pedro-pascal-vanessa-kirby-mcu-1851256106">Fantastic Four</a></span> are joining the roster. Mister Fantastic and Invisible Woman will join on January 10, seemingly alongside a new map, a balance patch, and a battle pass. The other two will join in the latter half of the season. Developer NetEase is rolling out information on Season 1: Eternal Night Falls throughout the week, so we’ll be updating this post with new details as they come. Here’s everything we know so far about <em>Marvel Rivals</em>’ Fantastic Four-focused season. - Kenneth Shepard <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/marvel-rivals-season-1-fantastic-four-patch-notes-map-1851733602&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/marvel-rivals-season-1-fantastic-four-patch-notes-map-1851733602">Read More</a></span></p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="745bf2b36b4dc7a5f2051d20cd480784" data-recommend-id="image://745bf2b36b4dc7a5f2051d20cd480784" data-format="jpg" data-width="1444" data-height="812" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="A PlayStation Portal hovers over a sphere." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="A PlayStation Portal hovers over a sphere." data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="fair-use" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Screenshot<!-- -->: <!-- -->Sony / Kotaku</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="745bf2b36b4dc7a5f2051d20cd480784" data-recommend-id="image://745bf2b36b4dc7a5f2051d20cd480784" data-format="jpg" data-width="1444" data-height="812" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="A PlayStation Portal hovers over a sphere." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>As updates have poured in throughout the last year or so, the <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;External link&quot;,&quot;https://g-o-media.digidip.net/visit?url=https%3A%2F%2Fdirect.playstation.com%2Fen-us%2Fbuy-accessories%2Fplaystation-portal-remote-player&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://g-o-media.digidip.net/visit?url=https%3A%2F%2Fdirect.playstation.com%2Fen-us%2Fbuy-accessories%2Fplaystation-portal-remote-player" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">PlayStation Portal</a></span> has become ever more attractive for on-the-go gaming (at least, as long as you have wi-fi available). It’s also perfect for streaming games while laid up in bed at night—or while taking care of some, uh, natural business if you’re so inclined.  - Billy Givens <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/ps-portal-headphones-wired-wireless-bluetooth-1851735677&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/ps-portal-headphones-wired-wireless-bluetooth-1851735677">Read More</a></span></p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="0f5054db98bd0756030bfb463fbb82ab" data-recommend-id="image://0f5054db98bd0756030bfb463fbb82ab" data-format="jpg" data-width="1280" data-height="720" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Shadow holds up a fist with an angry expression." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="Shadow holds up a fist with an angry expression." data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="false" data-imagerights="other-license" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->Paramount</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="0f5054db98bd0756030bfb463fbb82ab" data-recommend-id="image://0f5054db98bd0756030bfb463fbb82ab" data-format="jpg" data-width="1280" data-height="720" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Shadow holds up a fist with an angry expression." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>When I walked into a <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/sonic-hedgehog-3-shadow-master-emerald-build-a-bear-1851711339&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/sonic-hedgehog-3-shadow-master-emerald-build-a-bear-1851711339">Build-a-Bear Workshop</a></span> last month and they were completely sold out of their Shadow the Hedgehog bears to stuff and dress to your liking, I don’t think I expected it to be a harbinger for a plague of scalpers taking advantage of the <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/sonic-hedgehog-3-review-shadow-keanu-reeves-jim-carrey-1851726797&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/sonic-hedgehog-3-review-shadow-keanu-reeves-jim-carrey-1851726797"><em>Sonic the Hedgehog</em> </a></span>community. But it turns out that is exactly what it was, and I’m feeling very lucky to have stumbled into a store that gave me the display version of the doll they had on their shelf so I wouldn’t be stuck in the purgatory of resellers posting the Ultimate Lifeform on sites like eBay for hundreds of dollars. - Kenneth Shepard <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/sonic-hedgehog-3-shadow-build-a-bear-store-online-ebay-1851735236&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/sonic-hedgehog-3-shadow-build-a-bear-store-online-ebay-1851735236">Read More</a></span></p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="abce31ef45027cbbb3dffd1265c80073" data-recommend-id="image://abce31ef45027cbbb3dffd1265c80073" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Characters from Marvel Rivals go to battle with one another." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="Characters from Marvel Rivals go to battle with one another." data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="false" data-imagerights="other-license" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->Marvel Games</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="abce31ef45027cbbb3dffd1265c80073" data-recommend-id="image://abce31ef45027cbbb3dffd1265c80073" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Characters from Marvel Rivals go to battle with one another." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p><em>Marvel Rivals </em>features three types of heroes: Vanguards, Duelists, and <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/marvel-rivals-best-strategists-rocket-raccoon-jeff-shar-1851726466?rev=1734715605121&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/marvel-rivals-best-strategists-rocket-raccoon-jeff-shar-1851726466?rev=1734715605121">Strategists</a></span>. Arguably, the Vanguard can change the tide of battle the most. Traditionally known as tanks, the role of these heroes is to soak up damage to let the rest of their team invade the objective and make their way in.  - Parker Johnson <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/marvel-rivals-best-vanguard-peni-parker-venom-1851733445&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/marvel-rivals-best-vanguard-peni-parker-venom-1851733445">Read More</a></span></p></div></div></div>]]></content:encoded>
